  "text": "The nutrients provided by plant seeds are the basis for the growth and development of offspring. PLCPs are one of the key factors to initiate and complete this process [CITATION_1] . It is well known that seed germination may be destroyed under adversity stresses, resulting in the inability to form seedlings. Under stress conditions, the activity of PLCPs and their regulatory factors may be destroyed, but the specific mechanism of \"destruction\" and the resulting consequences need further analysis in various plants.",
